  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Forming a quadratic equation from the product of two expressions</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
The product of two expressions \((x + {@a@})\) and \((x + {@b@})\) is {@k@}.
Form a quadratic equation in \(x\) and write it in standard quadratic form.
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The statement “the product is {@k@}” means:
</p>

<p>
\[
(x + {@a@})(x + {@b@}) = {@k@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Expand the product.
</p>

<p>
\[
(x + {@a@})(x + {@b@}) = x^2 + ({@a+b@})x + {@a*b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
So the equation becomes:
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + ({@a+b@})x + {@a*b@} = {@k@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Rearrange to standard form by subtracting {@k@} from both sides.
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + ({@a+b@})x + {@a*b@} - {@k@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the required quadratic equation is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{x^2 + ({@a+b@})x + {@a*b - k@} = 0}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
